meanings.definition: To climb higher or faster than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: The determined squirrel managed to outclimb the other squirrels to reach the top of the tree.
meanings.sent2: The experienced hiker was able to outclimb his friends and reach the summit first.
meanings.sent3: The playful kitten tried to outclimb the dog, but ended up getting stuck in the tree.
meanings.sent4: The young athlete trained hard to outclimb his own limits and achieve new heights.
meanings.sent5: The competitive climbers raced to outclimb each other, pushing themselves to the peak.

meanings.sent1: The agile monkey could easily outclimb any other primate in the jungle.
meanings.sent2: She was determined to outclimb her fear of heights and conquer the mountain.
meanings.sent3: The spider tried to outclimb the raindrops falling on its web, but it was a slippery challenge.
meanings.sent4: The mountaineer had to outclimb the storm to reach the safety of the summit.
meanings.sent5: The rock climber had to outclimb the competition to win the championship.
